No. 2817. Aultman v. Utsey.

November Term, 1891.

December 23, 1891. per curiam

This was a petition for a rehearing of this case (34 S. C., 559), upon the grounds taken in the motion stated in No. 2819, next infra. The court ruled that the grounds taken were not appropriate to a petition for rehearing, but were properly presented by a motion to set aside the judgment. Application refused
